734	  \label{lem:gf_degreeOf_t_ne_of_ne}
735	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.GenericFreeness.degreeOf_t_ne_of_ne}
736	  \uses{lem:gf_degreeOf_zero_t, lem:gf_sum_r_mul_ne}
737	  For distinct support exponents \(v \ne w\) of \(f\) (both in \(\mathrm{supp}\,f\)), the
738	  transformed monomials \(T(c_v X^v)\) and \(T(c_w X^w)\) — with
739	  \(c_v = \mathrm{coeff}_v f\), \(c_w = \mathrm{coeff}_w f\) — have distinct degrees in
740	  \(X_0\). This is the key separation property making the top \(X_0\)-degree of \(T(f)\)
741	  unique.
